  "prompt": "Why is M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\"?",
  "response": "M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\" emphasizes the candy's unique design and coating, which allows it to maintain its shape and integrity even in warm conditions. The outer candy shell protects the chocolate from melting quickly, ensuring that consumers can enjoy the candy without it becoming messy. This tagline highlights one of the key selling points of M&M's\u2014 the convenience and enjoyment of eating the candy without the hassle of sticky fingers, making it an appealing choice for many snackers. It reflects the brand's focus on delivering a fun and pleasant candy experience.",
